62
00:06:55,410 --> 00:06:58,660
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, of course you haven't.

63
00:07:48,210 --> 00:07:50,550
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Allow me, miss. - Thank you, Katie.

64
00:07:59,140 --> 00:08:00,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's all right.

65
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, for heaven's sake. Um...

66
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Who shall I make it out to? - I'm sorry?

67
00:08:09,230 --> 00:08:11,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Please, Mr... - Mallory.

68
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:15,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr Mallory, you'll excuse my brevity,but this is my home.

69
00:08:15,490 --> 00:08:17,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Very glad you enjoyed the book. - I didn't.

70
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:21,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Excuse me? - I didn't much like your book.

71
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:24,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I found it too certain.

72
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:28,210
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Perhaps that's only fitting for someone so rude to strangers.

73
00:08:29,380 --> 00:08:33,420
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm a history master at a boy's prep school.

74
00:08:33,510 --> 00:08:35,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Forgive my daughter, Mr Mallory.

