{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're fine?

86
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mmm.

87
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:39,490
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We always know why you throw yourself into this.

88
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:43,990
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And we don't blame you for thinking that it will help.

89
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:49,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But every time now, all we can see is the pain it causes you.

90
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:00,470
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes.

91
00:10:01,470 --> 00:10:04,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know. I'm sorry I keep doing this to you.

92
00:10:05,470 --> 00:10:07,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's not fair.

93
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:29,210
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"May your skin be flayed from your body"

94
00:10:29,330 --> 00:10:32,380
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"in the hell you so arrogantly claim does not exist."

95
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:36,550
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}An elderly woman in Dorset, I seem to remember.

96
00:10:37,050 --> 00:10:40,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Our school matron is a devotee of your book

97
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:44,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and has told the headmaster about the work you do.

98
00:10:44,890 --> 00:10:46,560
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She assures him you're quite respected

99
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:50,890
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and your book sits alongside the Bible on many bookshelves.

100
00:10:51,020 --> 00:10:55,230
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Miss Cathcart, rumour is a dangerous thing.

101
00:10:56,570 --> 00:11:01,110
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Conversations in this room are confidential, Mr Mallory.

102
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,780
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Especially if I don't take the case.

103
00:11:06,910 --> 00:11:09,250
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Our school is called Rookford in Cumbria.

104
00:11:09,370 --> 00:11:13,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Some years ago, a child was said to have been murdered there.

105
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:15,880
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not a pupil. It was a private house then.

106
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:18,090
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, who? Did they catch the killer?

107
00:11:18,130 --> 00:11:21,420
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's no record. It was an important family. All hushed up.

108
00:11:21,550 --> 00:11:23,430
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Still, it's perfectly possible someone died there.

109
00:11:23,470 --> 00:11:26,430
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So you're here about a death that may or may not have happened

110
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}however many years ago?

111
00:11:28,140 --> 00:11:29,470
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No.

112
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:32,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm here about another death.

113
00:11:35,650 --> 00:11:39,480
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A pupil. Three weeks ago.

114
00:11:40,150 --> 00:11:43,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}His name was Walter. Walter Portman.

115
00:11:44,410 --> 00:11:47,660
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The day before he died, Walter went to see the headmaster,

116
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:50,830
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}quaking with fear, convinced he'd seen a ghost.

117
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The ghost of the murdered child.

118
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:55,330
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, how did he know what the murdered child looked like?

119
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:58,750
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This was taken 18 years ago.

120
00:12:04,430 --> 00:12:07,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr Mallory, this is... This is an old school prank.

121
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:08,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}As the camera sweeps across to expose the plate...

122
00:12:08,970 --> 00:12:11,520
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}One of the boys runs behind the row to appear at both sides.

123
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:13,980
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He was still moving when it reached him.

124
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:15,850
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know. That was 1902.

125
00:12:18,610 --> 00:12:20,650
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This was '03.

126
00:12:23,490 --> 00:12:25,110
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}'04.

127
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:27,990
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}1905.

128
00:12:28,030 --> 00:12:30,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And, lastly, '06.

129
00:12:30,870 --> 00:12:33,460
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All the boys in the school are accounted for.

130
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:35,500
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All of them. In all the photographs.

131
00:12:36,460 --> 00:12:40,130
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Including this one, taken just one month ago.

132
00:12:40,550 --> 00:12:43,050
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Miss Cathcart, I can understand a child running the length of the line

133
00:12:43,170 --> 00:12:46,340
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}in the 15 seconds it takes for the camera to make its sweep.

134
00:12:47,180 --> 00:12:50,510
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What I can't explain is how he could get there.

135
00:13:01,730 --> 00:13:03,360
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The Millford woman.

136
00:13:03,490 --> 00:13:06,860
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Either a batch of partially exposed photographic plates

137
00:13:06,910 --> 00:13:09,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}or the same ghost was in my mother's potting shed.

138
00:13:09,490 --> 00:13:10,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's half-term in two days.

139
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:12,830
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We'll be lucky to get any of the children back unless...

140
00:13:12,870 --> 00:13:15,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm not interested in the commercial fortunes of your school.

141
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:18,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There have been other sightings. The boys believe...

142
00:13:18,170 --> 00:13:21,340
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Boys believe in Santa Claus and the Tooth Fairy.

143
00:13:21,380 --> 00:13:23,170
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm sure some of them even believe in God.

144
00:13:25,090 --> 00:13:27,510
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You don't need me to tell you what happened

145
00:13:27,550 --> 00:13:29,890
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}to that generation of boys, Mr Mallory,

146
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:32,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and yet you don't see their ghosts stalking the halls of your school.

147
00:13:32,770 --> 00:13:36,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Rookford is a boarding school, Miss Cathcart.

148
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:39,900
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Most of the boys are as good as orphans.

149
00:13:41,730 --> 00:13:44,400
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't say that just because of your circumstances.

150
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:46,610
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, then, why say it?

151
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:53,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Fear is all I remember of my childhood.

152
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:55,750
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"I have glimpses of my parents' death

153
00:13:55,870 --> 00:13:58,790
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"but nothing of our life in Kenya, nor coming to London.

154
00:13:58,920 --> 00:14:01,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Nothing but a feeling of perpetual black terror."

155
00:14:03,710 --> 00:14:04,880
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your tactics are despicable.

156
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:08,090
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Fear swallows children and the adults we become."

157
00:14:09,590 --> 00:14:12,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}These boys aren't worried about bumps in the night.

158
00:14:13,140 --> 00:14:15,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They are frightened to death.

159
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:25,280
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Please leave.

160
00:14:29,610 --> 00:14:32,120
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I was sent to request your help and I've done that.

161
00:14:33,620 --> 00:14:35,950
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You strike me as a woman who won't do anything she doesn't want to.

162
00:14:38,790 --> 00:14:42,130
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm at the Wellington Hotel. Thank you for your time.

163
00:15:28,340 --> 00:15:30,630
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Semper veritas.

164
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:34,300
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Latin gives a new school an air of respectability.

165
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:36,350
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Means they can add a pound to the fees.

166
00:15:36,390 --> 00:15:39,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And I should imagine a bona fide ghost knocks it right off again.

167
00:15:40,060 --> 00:15:42,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Latin puns. What fun.

168
00:15:42,850 --> 00:15:44,560
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Always the truth."

169
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:47,360
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let's see, shall we?

170
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:48,860
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You can't wait.

171
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:51,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're that keen that people believe in nothing?

172
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:53,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, without science people don't believe in nothing.

173
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:56,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They believe in anything, including spirits.

174
00:15:56,160 --> 00:15:59,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So we need them. But you don't.

175
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:02,410
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I believe in evidence. Need has nothing to do with it.

176
00:16:02,540 --> 00:16:04,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And yet you carry someone else's cigarette case.

177
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:08,210
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Touche.

178
00:16:11,380 --> 00:16:12,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm sorry.

179
00:16:19,850 --> 00:16:21,520
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr Mallory, am I...

180
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:31,440
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Go on.

181
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:34,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Judd.

182
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:03,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey! Knees, boys!

183
00:17:46,980 --> 00:17:50,650
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Miss Cathcart, this is Miss Hill, the school matron. Maud to you and me.

184
00:17:50,770 --> 00:17:53,020
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- How do you do? - Maud?

185
00:17:56,950 --> 00:17:59,160
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She's taken this very hard.

186
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:03,200
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She's an odd fish at the best of times.

187
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:07,330
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}For a start, she liked your book.

188
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:17,670
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I feel like I know you.

189
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:19,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've read your book a dozen times at least.

190
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:22,350
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's on my bookshelf next to the Bible.

191
00:18:24,060 --> 00:18:26,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've never met an educated lady before.

192
00:18:26,810 --> 00:18:28,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not Cambridge and everything.

193
00:18:28,850 --> 00:18:31,190
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Never mind someone famous.

194
00:18:31,310 --> 00:18:33,690
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, the Kaiser was famous, Miss Hill.

195
00:18:33,730 --> 00:18:35,190
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I... I just wrote a book.

196
00:18:35,230 --> 00:18:36,860
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Maud.

197
00:18:37,530 --> 00:18:39,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr Mallory told you to call me Maud.

198
00:18:39,820 --> 00:18:41,410
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Maud.

199
00:18:41,990 --> 00:18:43,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Hello. - Hello.

200
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:49,160
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Did Mr McNair not say all boys inside, Thomas?

201
00:18:49,210 --> 00:18:50,710
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Tom.

202
00:18:53,710 --> 00:18:56,380
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Everyone's nerves are shot to pieces.

203
00:19:00,090 --> 00:19:03,430
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've been here 14 years. I know this place.

204
00:19:03,550 --> 00:19:06,560
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And I don't hold with any ghostly nonsense.

205
00:19:08,020 --> 00:19:11,020
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I just wanted you to know

206
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:14,020
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm at your service.

207
00:19:22,070 --> 00:19:23,740
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hello.

208
00:19:25,410 --> 00:19:27,410
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Stop it. Go on.

209
00:19:27,450 --> 00:19:30,410
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Howell, stick up for yourself. And get that hair cut.

210
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:32,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All of you, downstairs.

211
00:19:33,290 --> 00:19:35,590
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank you, Maud. I'll take Miss Cathcart to the headmaster.

212
00:19:38,590 --> 00:19:41,090
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Came with the building. It's the boys' favourite.

213
00:19:41,220 --> 00:19:44,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}John the Baptist, I think. This way.

214
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:47,430
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's actually Judith slaying Holofernes.

215
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:50,890
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Story of a woman who stole into the enemy camp

216
00:19:50,930 --> 00:19:54,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and seduced then beheaded their highest general.

217
00:19:54,980 --> 00:19:57,900
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hmm. Those were the days, eh, Maud?

218
00:20:01,150 --> 00:20:03,820
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm not in, I'm out.

219
00:20:04,780 --> 00:20:07,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}At least I was out. Now I'm in.

220
00:20:08,330 --> 00:20:10,790
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You must be the ghost lady. Come through.

221
00:20:10,910 --> 00:20:13,500
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Reverend Purslow, this is Miss Florence Cathcart.

222
00:20:13,620 --> 00:20:16,790
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}An educated woman. Well, well, well. Glad you're here.

223
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:18,750
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Presume you know you've a matron to thank.

224
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:21,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So I believe. Glad I can be of service.

225
00:20:21,130 --> 00:20:23,670
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Child dying before a parent. Dreadful thing.

226
00:20:24,300 --> 00:20:25,840
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I lost three of them.

227
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:28,800
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I imagine you don't believe in the afterlife, Miss Cathcart.

228
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:31,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, I don't.

229
00:20:32,350 --> 00:20:33,770
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Terrible, isn't it?

230
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:38,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr Mallory will give you a tour of the school.

231
00:20:38,610 --> 00:20:42,190
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm on my way to the dining room should you wish to see it.

232
00:20:52,330 --> 00:20:54,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr Mallory.

233
00:20:55,870 --> 00:20:57,460
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So I'm the guide now?

234
00:20:57,500 --> 00:21:00,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's coming. He's coming.

235
00:21:00,170 --> 00:21:04,050
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}After supper there's an hour of scrubs, that's compulsory reading to you.

236
00:21:04,170 --> 00:21:06,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Then lights out at 8:00.

237
00:21:07,340 --> 00:21:09,800
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll show you where Walter was found.

238
00:21:09,850 --> 00:21:13,520
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'd like to see everywhere the boys claim to have seen the ghost.

239
00:21:13,560 --> 00:21:16,690
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And perhaps you'd ask Maud to join us?

240
00:21:21,190 --> 00:21:24,690
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Most of the sightings were in here, including Walter's.

241
00:21:24,820 --> 00:21:29,160
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}In fact, he was found outside here on the terrace.

242
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:33,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Many of the boys are now too frightened to come in here.

243
00:21:33,830 --> 00:21:34,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr Mallory.

244
00:21:35,540 --> 00:21:39,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She doesn't like any superfluous sound.

245
00:21:43,510 --> 00:21:47,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Ego contemno Latin." I hate Latin.

246
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:50,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That you, Mallory?

247
00:21:56,020 --> 00:21:57,890
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Walter was found there.

248
00:21:58,020 --> 00:22:00,560
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr Broad found him just before breakfast.

249
00:22:00,730 --> 00:22:03,070
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- And these doors were locked? - Mmm-hmm.

250
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:16,790
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Did he have a bear or a toy animal?

251
00:22:16,910 --> 00:22:19,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- It's in the front office, yes. - Could you?

252
00:22:28,590 --> 00:22:29,970
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You don't like him.

253
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:34,810
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I have my reasons. It would be indiscreet.

254
00:22:39,060 --> 00:22:42,610
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where are his glasses? He used to keep up the pretence.

255
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:47,320
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Used to have a limp, too. Kept him out of the trenches.

256
00:22:49,110 --> 00:22:52,280
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- His mother couldn't bear to keep it. - Thank you.

257
00:22:53,620 --> 00:22:56,080
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And this was still on his bed the morning he was found?

258
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:57,660
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes.

259
00:22:58,250 --> 00:23:00,460
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You said there were other sightings elsewhere in the house?

260
00:23:00,580 --> 00:23:02,630
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes. Mostly in the west dormitory.

261
00:23:02,750 --> 00:23:04,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Maud, perhaps I could leave this to you?

262
00:23:12,840 --> 00:23:15,300
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Why aren't you at scrubs? - My book, sir.

263
00:23:15,850 --> 00:23:17,810
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Are you all right?

264
00:23:53,890 --> 00:23:55,550
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And it's half-term tomorrow?

265
00:23:55,680 --> 00:23:59,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Boys with parents in far-flung places stay behind.

