{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I came here to protect children from fear and you...

399
00:41:14,050 --> 00:41:15,970
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You are hell-bent on making them live in it.

400
00:41:16,050 --> 00:41:18,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You can't die of fear. - No.

401
00:41:18,550 --> 00:41:22,560
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But you can die of an asthma attack brought on by it.

402
00:41:38,870 --> 00:41:41,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- He was alive when I left him. - Malcolm.

403
00:41:43,250 --> 00:41:44,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He was crying,

404
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:47,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}insisting he'd seen a ghost.

405
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:51,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I thought...

406
00:41:52,840 --> 00:41:54,920
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I thought I'd toughen him up.

407
00:42:03,390 --> 00:42:06,520
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's not enough to be mollycoddled, Robert.

408
00:42:08,650 --> 00:42:10,690
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}These boys must be strong.

409
00:42:13,780 --> 00:42:15,400
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Stronger than us.

410
00:42:24,200 --> 00:42:27,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Malcolm, there's not a man on earth I'd rather protect.

411
00:42:28,670 --> 00:42:33,500
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But the parents arrive shortly, and I must ask you to leave this school

412
00:42:33,590 --> 00:42:34,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}at once.

413
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:12,500
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}? Be still, my soul

414
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:17,340
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}? Though dearest friends depart

415
00:43:28,890 --> 00:43:32,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There was a chap in a trench not far from ours.

416
00:43:32,230 --> 00:43:35,270
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He used to sing this hymn most sunsets.

417
00:43:38,690 --> 00:43:41,110
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's odd separating the past from the present.

418
00:43:47,200 --> 00:43:50,250
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The boys are transformed. You should be pleased.

419
00:43:56,050 --> 00:43:57,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Semper veritas.

420
00:43:58,460 --> 00:44:00,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Mmm. - Truth comes at a price.

421
00:44:02,550 --> 00:44:04,550
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Ruined a damaged man.

422
00:44:04,640 --> 00:44:06,970
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, I'm not thinking about Malcolm.

423
00:44:07,930 --> 00:44:09,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Nor are you.

424
00:44:11,230 --> 00:44:12,640
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I saw you.

425
00:44:13,770 --> 00:44:16,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}As soon as you proved the ghost was a fraud, something happened to you.

426
00:44:16,230 --> 00:44:17,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You were suddenly... - Please, Robert.

427
00:44:22,320 --> 00:44:24,570
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've done what was asked of me.

428
00:44:25,820 --> 00:44:27,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Proved there's nothing to fear.

429
00:44:31,660 --> 00:44:33,160
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Nothing.

430
00:44:57,520 --> 00:44:59,190
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You left church early.

431
00:45:01,110 --> 00:45:02,530
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr Judd.

432
00:45:02,780 --> 00:45:04,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You going home?

433
00:45:05,450 --> 00:45:06,950
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Found your ghost?

434
00:45:09,450 --> 00:45:13,710
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Another case to write up while McNair's thrown to the dogs.

435
00:45:14,120 --> 00:45:15,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}After all he's been through.

436
00:45:18,710 --> 00:45:21,300
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You know, I wonder whether any of us really know

437
00:45:21,380 --> 00:45:23,130
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}what he went through, Mr Judd.

438
00:45:23,550 --> 00:45:25,970
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You shouldn't talk to me like that. - Excuse me?

439
00:45:32,470 --> 00:45:35,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I'm sorry. I didn't mean to... - You think I don't know?

440
00:45:36,480 --> 00:45:38,560
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Staying at home was wrong?

441
00:45:40,400 --> 00:45:42,070
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come down here

442
00:45:42,900 --> 00:45:44,490
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and tell me that?

443
00:45:44,530 --> 00:45:47,530
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let me tell you something, ghost lady.

444
00:45:47,820 --> 00:45:50,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's the living you wanna watch out for.

445
00:45:52,080 --> 00:45:53,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not the dead.

446
00:46:04,340 --> 00:46:08,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There she is. Now try to forget all about it. The headmaster will.

447
00:46:09,550 --> 00:46:12,890
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Getting to go home. Cakes and puddings.

448
00:46:13,680 --> 00:46:15,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Lucky beggars.

449
00:46:15,890 --> 00:46:18,230
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Still, we'll have a nice time.

450
00:46:19,350 --> 00:46:20,860
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You always say that.

451
00:46:21,770 --> 00:46:24,780
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Lucky beggars. You always say that.

452
00:47:08,400 --> 00:47:09,610
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No!

453
00:47:28,590 --> 00:47:38,640
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's nothing.

454
00:48:10,630 --> 00:48:13,300
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Goodbye. See you in a week.

455
00:48:13,390 --> 00:48:16,470
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Check the out buildings before you go, Mr Baxter.

456
00:48:16,560 --> 00:48:18,470
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There are gypsies on the Tarrow farm.

457
00:48:29,320 --> 00:48:31,440
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your ma and pa overseas, Tom?

458
00:48:31,820 --> 00:48:33,650
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They live in India.

459
00:48:33,780 --> 00:48:38,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Takes three weeks to travel to India. They have tigers there.

460
00:48:39,330 --> 00:48:40,950
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Goodbye, Matron.

461
00:48:41,330 --> 00:48:42,830
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mary.

462
00:48:44,040 --> 00:48:45,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Have you been?

463
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:47,460
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No.

464
00:48:48,380 --> 00:48:51,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, but I've seen the lions in Africa.

465
00:48:52,170 --> 00:48:54,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}One of them even attacked me.

466
00:48:55,840 --> 00:48:58,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How come you're not dead?

467
00:48:58,810 --> 00:49:01,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Apparently I was rescued by one of the villagers.

468
00:49:01,850 --> 00:49:04,020
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Actually, a tribal chieftain.

469
00:49:04,560 --> 00:49:06,020
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Did he kill the lion?

470
00:49:06,060 --> 00:49:08,190
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I was very young. I think so.

471
00:49:09,520 --> 00:49:13,320
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The villagers took me in and looked after me until help came.

472
00:49:14,240 --> 00:49:16,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They called me their "Mowa-Zee".

473
00:49:17,870 --> 00:49:19,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}White doll.

474
00:49:23,250 --> 00:49:25,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I wonder what they'd think of me today, seeing me in such a silly state.

475
00:49:25,920 --> 00:49:29,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Tom, can you leave us now? - Were your mother and father with you?

476
00:49:30,550 --> 00:49:32,000
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Were they killed?

477
00:49:32,670 --> 00:49:34,050
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Afraid they were.

478
00:49:34,090 --> 00:49:36,380
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Tom, Miss Cathcart and I want a grown-up conversation.

479
00:49:36,430 --> 00:49:37,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I like grown-up conversations.

480
00:49:38,050 --> 00:49:39,510
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now.

481
00:49:42,430 --> 00:49:44,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Goodbye, Mowa-Zee.

482
00:49:51,900 --> 00:49:55,240
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Maud, it was an accident.

483
00:49:55,780 --> 00:49:57,360
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I lost my cigarette case.

484
00:49:57,410 --> 00:49:59,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How could someone like you want to do such a thing?

485
00:49:59,410 --> 00:50:00,740
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't want to talk about it.

486
00:50:00,870 --> 00:50:03,290
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't go. Miss, something has happened to you.

487
00:50:03,410 --> 00:50:04,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You can't leave this house now.

488
00:50:05,040 --> 00:50:08,080
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Please stop calling me miss. It's Florence.

489
00:50:09,080 --> 00:50:10,880
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And I can't stay here.

490
00:50:12,250 --> 00:50:13,920
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm sorry.

491
00:50:30,980 --> 00:50:32,480
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank you.

492
00:50:35,320 --> 00:50:36,990
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll be gone in an hour.

493
00:50:45,290 --> 00:50:50,330
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I fell.

494
00:53:17,980 --> 00:53:19,820
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know you're there, Robert.

495
00:53:23,280 --> 00:53:24,950
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Please don't go away.

496
00:53:38,960 --> 00:53:40,590
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't go.

497
00:54:43,860 --> 00:54:45,820
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You must be the ghost lady.

498
00:54:47,650 --> 00:54:49,070
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come through.

499
00:54:55,410 --> 00:54:57,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good evening.

500
00:54:57,080 --> 00:54:58,710
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good evening.

501
00:55:59,390 --> 00:56:01,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Be quiet.

502
00:56:01,440 --> 00:56:03,440
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You'll be quiet or so helo me!

503
00:56:14,120 --> 00:56:15,740
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr Mallory, I need your help.

504
00:56:15,780 --> 00:56:17,120
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're not going?

505
00:56:17,160 --> 00:56:18,950
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Some of the equipment needs resetting.

506
00:56:19,080 --> 00:56:20,450
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Can I... - I don't understand.

507
00:56:20,620 --> 00:56:22,790
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You have your culprit. You're doing more?

508
00:56:23,460 --> 00:56:25,290
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Oh, would you... - No, thank you.

509
00:56:25,420 --> 00:56:27,290
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't you like sherry?

510
00:56:27,340 --> 00:56:29,460
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I need to keep my wits about me.

511
00:56:30,510 --> 00:56:32,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't think I shall ever drink alcohol.

512
00:56:32,800 --> 00:56:35,260
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- It makes you cross and sick. - Mr Judd,

513
00:56:35,930 --> 00:56:37,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}you're welcome to join us.

514
00:56:37,970 --> 00:56:40,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Things to do, Matron.

515
00:56:40,930 --> 00:56:42,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mallory.

516
00:56:44,480 --> 00:56:45,900
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr Mallory.

517
00:56:47,570 --> 00:56:48,980
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Florence, what are you doing?

518
00:56:49,070 --> 00:56:51,400
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I was brought here to explain a phenomenon in this house,

519
00:56:51,490 --> 00:56:54,820
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and whatever everyone else may believe, I have yet to do that.

520
00:56:54,990 --> 00:56:58,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A collective delusion has been experienced here,

521
00:56:58,490 --> 00:57:02,160
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}a child moving through the house as if there were no walls or floors.

522
00:57:03,500 --> 00:57:05,710
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You said that a child was murdered here.

523
00:57:05,830 --> 00:57:07,500
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What if that was also caused by...

524
00:57:07,590 --> 00:57:09,590
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're doing this because of a feeling?

525
00:57:09,670 --> 00:57:12,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- This morning, you were... - This is not a feeling!

526
00:57:12,720 --> 00:57:15,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This is a thesis. It's science.

527
00:57:15,840 --> 00:57:19,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Tell me about the original murder. - One can't even be sure there was one.

528
00:57:19,220 --> 00:57:22,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Something is causing this. - Two hours ago, you...

529
00:57:24,600 --> 00:57:26,400
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Florence, why are you doing this? - Florence.

530
00:57:32,030 --> 00:57:34,610
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- What is it? - A differential thermometer.

531
00:57:34,740 --> 00:57:38,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It means this side of the corridor has suddenly become

532
00:57:38,200 --> 00:57:40,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}much colder than that side.

533
00:57:40,450 --> 00:57:43,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You said this was a private house.

534
00:57:45,580 --> 00:57:48,750
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Housemaids often had hidden cupboards

535
00:57:48,880 --> 00:57:52,710
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}for mops and brooms and so forth.

536
00:57:58,550 --> 00:58:02,060
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}May even be stairs to the upper levels.

537
00:58:45,640 --> 00:58:47,940
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know this.

538
00:58:48,350 --> 00:58:49,770
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's an old nursery rhyme.

539
00:58:53,110 --> 00:58:55,780
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Ladybird, ladybird,

540
00:58:55,860 --> 00:58:58,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}fly away home.

541
00:59:00,280 --> 00:59:02,120
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your house is on fire.

542
00:59:04,290 --> 00:59:06,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your children are gone.

543
00:59:10,670 --> 00:59:12,210
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All except one.

544
00:59:16,130 --> 00:59:18,220
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We need to work. Lock the house.

545
00:59:18,300 --> 00:59:20,630
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Florence, you don't need... - Robert, lock the house.

546
00:59:25,220 --> 00:59:27,560
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This is nothing, it's a silly nursery rhyme.

547
00:59:27,640 --> 00:59:29,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm frightened.

548
00:59:29,480 --> 00:59:30,520
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Tom.

549
00:59:30,650 --> 00:59:33,020
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Tom. - He wants to get me.

550
00:59:34,650 --> 00:59:36,980
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Tom, nothing is going to happen to you. Nothing.

551
00:59:37,820 --> 00:59:39,320
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I promise you that.

552
00:59:40,700 --> 00:59:43,490
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now I must work. I'll be upstairs if you need me.

553
01:00:25,280 --> 01:00:27,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Can I sit with you? I won't talk.

554
01:00:27,740 --> 01:00:29,200
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Of course.

555
01:00:38,210 --> 01:00:40,050
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I get in trouble for talking.

556
01:00:42,930 --> 01:00:44,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But I don't talk much.

557
01:00:46,890 --> 01:00:48,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Did you have any friends at school?

558
01:00:50,220 --> 01:00:52,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You can talk to me.

559
01:00:55,480 --> 01:00:58,690
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I have make-believe friends. Sometimes.

560
01:00:58,820 --> 01:01:02,570
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's nothing wrong with that. Many children do. I know I did.

561
01:01:03,570 --> 01:01:05,240
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What was his name?

562
01:01:08,830 --> 01:01:10,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm not sure he had a name.

563
01:01:12,160 --> 01:01:15,080
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Do yours have names? - You're still lonely.

564
01:01:15,170 --> 01:01:16,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Aren't you?

565
01:01:20,250 --> 01:01:21,670
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I can tell.

566
01:01:22,170 --> 01:01:23,970
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}With the boys at school, too,

567
01:01:24,380 --> 01:01:26,090
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I can tell.

568
01:01:28,930 --> 01:01:30,890
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You had a real friend once.

569
01:01:31,810 --> 01:01:33,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And you don't any more.

570
01:01:34,890 --> 01:01:36,770
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Did you love him or something?

571
01:01:41,900 --> 01:01:43,530
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes, I loved him.

572
01:01:45,450 --> 01:01:47,570
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He was a very kind man, a very good man.

573
01:01:55,080 --> 01:01:56,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But I was...

574
01:01:58,420 --> 01:02:01,290
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I did something very silly and very cruel.

575
01:02:04,380 --> 01:02:07,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I think I was frightened of losing him, I loved him so much.

576
01:02:10,640 --> 01:02:12,220
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He was in the war.

577
01:02:13,350 --> 01:02:14,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What did you do?

578
01:02:16,310 --> 01:02:17,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I wrote to him and told him

579
01:02:17,810 --> 01:02:20,270
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I couldn't marry him and I didn't love him any more.

580
01:02:21,980 --> 01:02:23,570
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What did he say?

581
01:02:26,860 --> 01:02:28,450
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He died.

582
01:02:30,370 --> 01:02:31,950
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not long after he got the letter.

583
01:02:32,160 --> 01:02:33,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But you did love him.

584
01:02:35,160 --> 01:02:36,790
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's why you want him back.

585
01:02:51,640 --> 01:02:53,850
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank you. Mowa-Zee.

586
01:03:03,440 --> 01:03:04,900
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't think there's a place on earth

587
01:03:04,980 --> 01:03:08,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}people understand loneliness better than here.

588
01:03:25,670 --> 01:03:29,510
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're torturing yourself. Is that what you're doing here?

589
01:03:29,630 --> 01:03:31,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Proving again and again that he's really gone?

590
01:03:32,300 --> 01:03:34,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Twisting the blade in deeper? - You tell me.

591
01:03:34,760 --> 01:03:35,850
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why? Is it guilt?

592
01:03:35,930 --> 01:03:37,430
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Preaching to me while you rip your leg to shreds

593
01:03:37,520 --> 01:03:39,980
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}as if that'll make you feel better for having survived!

594
01:03:46,570 --> 01:03:48,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You don't know what you're talking about.

595
01:03:54,450 --> 01:03:55,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Robert.

596
01:03:57,410 --> 01:03:58,830
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm frightened.

597
01:03:59,540 --> 01:04:01,000
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And I can't live with that.

598
01:04:01,250 --> 01:04:03,170
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And yes, you're right, what I do comes at a price.

599
01:04:03,250 --> 01:04:06,880
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I hate myself more and more, but I can't live with fear.

600
01:04:08,710 --> 01:04:10,420
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'd sooner be dead myself.

601
01:05:23,210 --> 01:05:26,250
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Red four goes on the black five.

602
01:05:26,960 --> 01:05:29,880
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Every card has its place.

603
01:05:29,960 --> 01:05:32,670
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}When they're back where they should be, you win the game.

604
01:05:33,880 --> 01:05:35,340
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And that goes there.

605
01:05:37,010 --> 01:05:39,050
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That one there.

606
01:05:40,390 --> 01:05:43,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Black eight can go on red nine.

607
01:05:44,940 --> 01:05:46,440
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It takes time.

608
01:05:47,610 --> 01:05:49,520
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's why they call it "patience".

609
01:05:57,660 --> 01:05:59,410
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She's downstairs.

610
01:07:14,690 --> 01:07:17,650
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Mowa-Zee. - Tom. Tom!

611
01:07:18,200 --> 01:07:19,650
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Tom!

612
01:07:25,620 --> 01:07:27,410
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know it's you, Tom.

613
01:07:28,370 --> 01:07:30,000
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I won't chase you.

614
01:07:30,580 --> 01:07:32,000
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Keep playing.

615
01:08:13,540 --> 01:08:15,000
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Florence.

616
01:08:22,760 --> 01:08:25,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why are you doing this? You!

617
01:08:25,470 --> 01:08:27,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I heard you giggle.

618
01:08:27,260 --> 01:08:28,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I heard him giggle. - Florence!

619
01:08:28,770 --> 01:08:31,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You took me to a man. Who was he? Who was he?

620
01:08:31,810 --> 01:08:34,650
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There was a... There was a man! There was... There was a man!

621
01:08:34,730 --> 01:08:35,810
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Stop this!

622
01:08:36,650 --> 01:08:38,480
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's... It's all of you!

623
01:08:38,940 --> 01:08:40,490
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're all doing this!

624
01:08:40,650 --> 01:08:42,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You, you...

625
01:08:42,150 --> 01:08:44,280
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You cruel and horrid little boy.

626
01:08:45,870 --> 01:08:47,200
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Florence!

627
01:08:48,200 --> 01:08:49,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I hate you.

628
01:08:52,540 --> 01:08:55,380
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thomas Hill, you will come back here at once and apologise.

629
01:08:55,500 --> 01:08:58,840
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Stop bossing me around. I haven't done anything wrong.

630
01:09:02,220 --> 01:09:04,130
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't recognise you.

631
01:09:04,220 --> 01:09:07,640
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I thought you were a kind, loving girl but there's...

632
01:09:08,890 --> 01:09:10,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's nothing left.

633
01:09:16,230 --> 01:09:17,980
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're a shell.

634
01:09:33,410 --> 01:09:35,210
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She's very troubled.

635
01:09:41,010 --> 01:09:43,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You have to understand that.

636
01:09:48,350 --> 01:09:50,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She likes you very, very much.

637
01:09:59,060 --> 01:10:00,860
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She doesn't care about me.

638
01:10:02,570 --> 01:10:04,690
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I may as well be dead like Walter.

639
01:10:06,700 --> 01:10:08,110
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I hate her.

640
01:10:35,810 --> 01:10:38,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Robert, I need your help.

641
01:10:41,820 --> 01:10:45,110
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He had a shotgun, and he was there,

642
01:10:45,650 --> 01:10:47,820
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and one of these will prove it.

643
01:10:52,490 --> 01:10:56,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I can leave an amber light on, but are you...

644
01:10:58,670 --> 01:11:00,330
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll be fine.

645
01:11:12,970 --> 01:11:15,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If you could just lift them.

646
01:11:18,020 --> 01:11:19,440
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's good.

647
01:11:21,480 --> 01:11:23,520
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The dark used to bother me.

648
01:11:24,610 --> 01:11:27,860
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Later, of course, it came to mean safety, no sniper fire, or...

649
01:11:28,200 --> 01:11:30,530
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Thank you. ...shells, but

650
01:11:32,620 --> 01:11:34,990
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}as a lad I'd huddle into my bed,

651
01:11:36,790 --> 01:11:40,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}wanting to see what was there but too frightened to open my eyes.

652
01:11:43,460 --> 01:11:44,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank you.

653
01:11:46,170 --> 01:11:49,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's never darker than when we close our eyes and yet we keep them shut.

654
01:11:53,470 --> 01:11:54,890
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why is that?

655
01:11:57,390 --> 01:11:59,140
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank you.

656
01:12:09,190 --> 01:12:12,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The motion's not blurred, so even if he's moving

657
01:12:12,990 --> 01:12:15,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}one of these will have him clearly.

658
01:12:16,200 --> 01:12:18,200
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why do you keep your eyes closed, Florence?

659
01:12:24,080 --> 01:12:25,590
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where is he?

660
01:12:30,090 --> 01:12:31,550
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, God.

661
01:12:40,230 --> 01:12:41,770
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No.

662
01:14:32,090 --> 01:14:33,880
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're real.

663
01:14:38,340 --> 01:14:39,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I am.

664
01:14:44,730 --> 01:14:49,730
